A Marakwet clan in Kerio Valley has been accused of sheltering bandits who attempted to raid a GSU camp.Members of Kapsiren clan on Tuesday said the Kabshoi clan accommodated the attackers on Monday night. Kapsiren reportedly threatened to attack the Kabshoi for aiding Pokot attackers.One person was injured on Tuesday after suspected Pokot bandits from Baringo attempted to attack a GSU camp in Marakwet East.The two clans have been fighting over land at Tot. Elgeyo Marakwet police commander Sharif Abdallah said more officers have been deployed to restore calm. Officers will quell retaliatory attacks, Abdallah said. He said the attacks have been fuelled by the high number of illegal firearms in the hands of civilians.